{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry includes transaldolases type 3B and fructose-6-phosphate aldolase. They share a high degree of structural similarity and sequence identity.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>Transaldolase ([ec:2.2.1.2]) catalyses the reversible transfer of a three-carbon ketol unit from sedoheptulose 7-phosphate to glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate to form erythrose 4-phosphate and fructose 6-phosphate. This enzyme, together with transketolase, provides a link between the glycolytic and pentose-phosphate pathways. Transaldolase is an enzyme of about 34kDa whose sequence has been well conserved throughout evolution. A lysine has been implicated [[cite:PUB00005649]] in the catalytic mechanism of the enzyme; it acts as a nucleophilic group that attacks the carbonyl group of fructose-6-phosphate.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>Fructose-6-phosphate aldolase was originally thought to be transaldolases or transaldolase-related proteins. However, they perform a novel reaction, the cleavage or formation of fructose 6-phosphate [[cite:PUB00053971]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "3r8r", "name" "Transaldolase from Bacillus subtilis"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR013785", "name" "Aldolase-type TIM barrel", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR00875" "fructose-6-phosphate aldolase"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Transaldolase type 3B/Fructose-6-phosphate aldolase", "short" "Transaldolase_3B/F6P_aldolase"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 22, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 3513, "taxa" 14067, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 16410, "sets" 0, "proteins" 16410, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 12799}, "pathways" 4}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "descrip